{"tid":1370191,"cid":24,"subCid":0,"title":"澳洲外長：不會容許中國侵犯澳洲言論自由","createTime":"2019-07-27T02:18:50.000Z","updateTime":"2019-07-29T06:10:10.000Z","uid":41404,"like":87,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":13,"replies":[{"pid":"87bc1be1320d5bfa45fb574ce2c3ce97b63005c0","tid":1370191,"uid":41404,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-27T02:18:50.000Z","msg":"Foreign Minister Marise Payne has warned that the Morrison government won&rsquo;t tolerate foreign interference in the exercise of free speech in Australia, after a senior Chinese diplomat backed &ldquo;patriotic behaviour&rdquo; by Chinese students who clashed violently with pro-Hong Kong protesters at the University of Queensland.<br />\n<br />\nSenator Payne warned that Australia expected foreign diplomats to respect Australia&rsquo;s rights to free speech and lawful protest, &ldquo;even on contentious and sensitive issues&rdquo;. &ldquo;The government would be particularly concerned if any foreign diplomatic mission were to act in ways that could undermine such rights, including by encouraging disruptive or &shy;potentially violent behaviour,&rdquo; she said.<br />\n<br />\nThe warning followed a statement by Chinese consul-general in Brisbane Xu Jie, who praised Chinese students for confronting what he said were &ldquo;anti-China separatist&rdquo; protesters with &ldquo;ulterior motives&rdquo; at UQ this week.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The consulate general attaches great importance to the safety of Chinese students, affirms the spontaneous patriotic behaviour of Chinese students, resolutely opposes the words and deeds of any separatist countries, and opposes the use of these events to create the opposition between Chinese and Hong Kong students and &shy;incite anti-China sentiment,&rdquo; he said."},{"pid":"633f8413bbfff37fde41de6457c8c90b2f4a058c","tid":1370191,"uid":191701,"like":8,"dislike":0,"score":8,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-07-27T02:20:19.000Z","msg":"中共一直想稱霸世界"},{"pid":"466aeb0deb3c3b22